<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-19T05:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-19T05:29:00-05:00" n="120" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/425</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-19T14:00:00+03:31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 23, 2.50
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1531. Quiet prevailed throughout yesterday and last night. Loyal
                                troops arrived from front, number unknown. Are now surrounding
                                palace on other side Neva which been headquarters Bolsheviks and
                                which near <persName>Peter Paul</persName> prison where Sturmer,
                                Protopopov and others confined.<note n="1" xml:id="d120fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_3">p.
                                    3</ref>.</note> Reported that prison garrison will aid
                                Bolsheviks if resistance offered but uncertain.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>